I"O<p>Rosenblatt’s Perceptron model was one of the first <a class="internal-link" href="/secondbrain/neural-networks-are-a-massive-conceptual-gateway">neural network</a> models with a <a class="internal-link" href="/secondbrain/supervised-learning-assumes-underlying-structure">learning</a> algorithm. An artificial retina is connected to an array of associators which are weighted before being plugged through a non-linear function. However, Rosenblatt hasn’t even considered <a class="internal-link" href="/secondbrain/regularization-penalizes-flexibility">overfitting</a> back then.</p>
